  "notes": [
    "Matchday 1 fixtures shown above (June 11-18 WIB). Matchdays 2-3 (through June 27) and the knockout stage will be added as the tournament progresses.",
    "Times converted from ET (UTC-4) to WIB (UTC+7, +11h). Some kickoff times/venues are provisional (TBD) pending confirmation from official sources.",
    "Group A is complete for Matchday 1: Mexico 2-0 South Africa (3 red cards, a World Cup record for an opening match) and South Korea 2-1 Czechia.",
    "Canada made history with a 1-1 draw against Bosnia-Herzegovina in the first men's World Cup match played on Canadian soil - Canada's first-ever World Cup point.",
    "United States beat Paraguay 4-1 at SoFi Stadium in Inglewood to open Group D (13 June, kickoff 08:00 WIB) - an own goal by Damian Bobadilla and a brace from Folarin Balogun put the USMNT 3-0 up before Paraguay substitute Mauricio scored a consolation goal in the 73rd minute, and Gio Reyna struck a late stoppage-time winner (90+8') assisted by Tim Weah to make it 4-1, a record margin for a USMNT World Cup match.",
    "Qatar 1-1 Switzerland (Group B) finished at Levi's Stadium - Switzerland led 1-0 at half-time via a Breel Embolo penalty (16'), but Qatar equalized in the second half. Brazil vs Morocco (Group C) is underway at MetLife Stadium - level 1-1 at half-time (Saibari 20' for Morocco, Vinícius Júnior 31' for Brazil); Haiti vs Scotland kicks off next.",
    "This page updates automatically 3x/day (04:00, 08:00, 12:00 WIB) with the latest scores, scorers, assists, cards, and standings."
